==== Decade 1970-1979 ====
The first two seasons of the 1970's, Nea Salamis ended in the middle of the table, while the next two relegation threatened eventually escaped an attempt toward the end of periods. The most tragic day in the history of the club recorded on August 14, 1974, with the occupation of Famagusta by the Turkish troops since the [[Turkish invasion of Cyprus|Turkish invasion of Cyprus]], which made the club as a refugee club<ref name="<U+0391><U+039C><U+039C>1"></ref>. The fans and the players of the club scattered to all free areas of Cyprus and abroad. In October, some members of the board met at the house of Aris Limassol. There it was decided to revive the club.<ref name=1974S>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=90}}</ref> Criterion for temporary office location was the presence of living material in the group. Most players of Nea Salamina were in Larnaca and thus taken a decision this city to be the temporarily ground of the football department.<ref name=1974S></ref> Initially, Nea Salamina housed temporarily at the house of Alki. January acquired its own building, with rent. In the early stages of the expenses were covered by contributions from members and friends of the club. Alongside started two football ranks, one in Larnaca and one in Limassol for training young players<ref name=S126></ref>.

Before the end of 1974, CFA decided to hold a special league. There was concern about the involvement of the team, because of the huge problems caused by the refugees, however, decided to participate. The aim was not so much distinction as to survive and stay in the first division.<ref name=1974S2>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=92}}</ref> As there was a permanent stadium, in the period 1974-75 used the GSZ Stadium<ref name=1974S2></ref>, in the period 1975-76 municipal stadium of [[Dherynia]],<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=91}}</ref> the period 1976-77 returned to GSZ stadium<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=95}}</ref>, in the period 1977-78 used [[Dasaki Stadium]] in Dasaki Achnas<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=96}}</ref> and the period 1978-79 returned to GSZ stadium{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=97}}</ref> where remained during the period 1979-80<ref name=1974S3>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=99}}</ref>.

Stay in first division had achieved by 1979. However, in the period [[1978-79 Cypriot First Division|1978-79]], although it had good start, Nea Salamina demoted the last game in the second division, after 25 years of continuous presence in the first division. Decisive was the last match of the tournament, when the stay was dependent effects of opponents. Nea Salamina faced [[Enosis Neon Paralimni FC]] and won 3-2. At the same time, it needed Evagoras not to beat champion Omonia or lose Olympiacos from Alki. Eventually, Evagoras won Omonia and Olympiakos bore draw with Alki<ref name=1974S3></ref>. Five teams have won more than one point of Nea Salamina and relegated so (although it had achieved 10 victories), while expressing grievances and leaving many innuendos about rigged games against<ref>{{harvnb|Gavreilides|Papamoiseos|2001|p=104}}</ref>. The period 1978-79 for the first time applied the dual relegation, while all previous relegation was single or not true at all.

In the summer of 1974, before the turkish invasion, Nea Salamis had agreed to cooperate with Bulgarian coach [[Iancho Arsov]], who decades laters won titles with Omonia. The arrival of coach in Cyprus and the agreement was canceled because it was impossible for a foreigner coach to be employed<ref name=S126>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=126}}</ref>.

