==== Decade 1980-1989 ====
During the period 1979-80 Nea Salamis played in the second division and was triumphant march. Many times fans at matches of Nea Salamina outnumbered fans racing first division. Comfortably won the league and returned to the first division in the period [[1980<U+2013>81 Cypriot First Division|1980-81]]<ref name=1974S3></ref><ref>{{harvnb|Gavreilides|Papamoiseos|2001|p=106}}</ref>. The first race won the later champion Omonia, a 2-1 away at [[Makario Stadium]] in Nicosia. This defeat of Omonia was the first suffered at Makario Stadium since started competing in it<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=104}}</ref>. Nea Salamis claimed high position in the league, but eventually finished seventh.<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=105}}</ref>

The period [[1981<U+2013>82 Cypriot First Division|1981-82]] Nea Salamina acquired for the first time foreign footballers: Bulgarian [[Nazca Michailiof]] and [[Stefan Pavlov]]<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=107}}</ref>. The period [[1982<U+2013>83 Cypriot First Division|1982-83]] was an unprecedented incident. In the game with opponent [[Enosis Neon Paralimni FC]] in GSZ stadium three players of Nea Salamina expelled so the remaining players surrounded the linesman to protest. The supervisor claimed that blows received thus transported to the hospital, but denied the radiographs. After termination of the supervisor, the case was brought to court imposed a sentence of 45 days. This was unprecedented for Cypriot football. The players remained in jail for five days and released after public outcry, but then the court of CFA crippling sanctions imposed on them as a result to stay for several months off the court.<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=109}}</ref><ref name="KOS">{{cite web|url=http://www.sentragoal.com.cy/article.asp?catid=18868&subid=2&pubid=128907664 |title=<U+00AB><U+0388><U+03B3><U+03BA><U+03BB><U+03B7><U+03BC><U+03B1> <U+03BA><U+03B1><U+03B9> <U+03C4><U+03B9><U+03BC><U+03C9><U+03C1><U+03AF><U+03B1>...<U+00BB>  |accessdate=2012-08-02|date=2011-12-26|work= |publisher=SentraGoal <U+039A><U+03CD><U+03C0><U+03C1><U+03BF><U+03C5> }}</ref>

The next football season was not accompanied by discrimination, but Nea Salamina succeeded many times score wins over champions. Untill 1985 used GSZ stadium as ground. In perido 1985-86 used two ground. In seven games played in Municipal Stadium of Deryneia, while the other six in the GSZ stadium<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=115}}</ref>. Then implementation started training premises owned Nea Salamis near the settlement of Tsiakillerou<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=117}}</ref>. The period 1986-87 used GSZ stadium<ref>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=118}}</ref>. From 1987-88 seat football department was the venue of Anorthosis, [[Antonis Papadopoulos Stadium]] in Larnaca.<ref name=S123>{{harvnb|Stilianou|Neofitou|1988|p=123}}</ref> This year completed proprietary sports club of the refugee settlement Tsakkilerou beside the court training the football team, volunteer work and offer hundreds of friends of the club.<ref name=S123></ref> The period 1988-89, after a good run finishing in fourth place while the cup came close to its participation in the final but was excluded from the subsequent winners AEL Limassol. During this period, footballer of Nea Salamina, [[Nigel Maknil]], was named the league's top scorer with 19 goals.<ref name=SKORER>{{harvnb|Gavreilides|Papamoiseos|2001|p=160}}</ref>

