== Turkish Cypriot  ==
Since its inception, Nea Salamina sought to develop friendly relations with the [[Turkish Cypriots]] community in Famagusta. An important element is the participation of Turkish Cypriots accepting players in a football team. In the early 1950's joined the team of Nea Salamis Turkish Cypriots footballers (Siekkeris, Nita, Moustafa etc.). When he joined the CFA, struggled for two seasons in the Second Division and had as rivals Turkish Cypriotclubs (eg Demir Sports, Kenslik Kiounslou, Turkish Club of Famagusta). When the Turkish Cypriot clubs began in late 1955 to withdraw from the tournaments of CFA, Nea Salamina made efforts to convince and to continue. Despite the withdrawal of Turkish Cypriot clubs from the CFA, the Turkish players remained welcome in Nea Salamina. In 1962 he was transferred to New Salamis Kallikas and in 1970 the Turkish origin Neziak.<ref name=ST98149>{{harvnb|Stilianou|1998|p=149}}</ref> In 2004 was transferred to Nea Salamis Turkish Cypriots Imam and Oulousoi, who with their presence at Nea Salamis became the first Turkish footballers who took part in the championships of CAF after thirty years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.pathfinder.gr/sports/176723.html |title=<U+039A><U+03CD><U+03C0><U+03C1><U+03BF><U+03C2> : <U+039F> <U+03B1><U+03B8><U+03BB><U+03B7><U+03C4><U+03B9><U+03C3><U+03BC><U+03CC><U+03C2> <U+03B5><U+03BD><U+03CE><U+03BD><U+03B5><U+03B9> ... |accessdate=2012-09-10 |date=2005-03-26 |work= |publisher=SportNet}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kathimerini.com.cy/index.php?pageaction=kat&modid=1&artid=48610&show=Y |title=<U+039F> <U+03BA><U+03B1><U+03BB><U+03CD><U+03C4><U+03B5><U+03C1><U+03BF><U+03C2> <U+03A4><U+03BF><U+03C5><U+03C1><U+03BA><U+03BF><U+03BA><U+03CD><U+03C0><U+03C1><U+03B9><U+03BF><U+03C2> <U+03C0><U+03BF><U+03B4><U+03BF><U+03C3><U+03C6><U+03B1><U+03B9><U+03C1><U+03B9><U+03C3><U+03C4><U+03AE><U+03C2> <U+03C0><U+03AC><U+03B5><U+03B9> <U+0391><U+03BB><U+03BA><U+03AE> |accessdate=2012-09-10 |date=2011-06-13 |work= |publisher=<U+0395><U+03C6><U+03B7><U+03BC><U+03B5><U+03C1><U+03AF><U+03B4><U+03B1> <U+039A><U+03B1><U+03B8><U+03B7><U+03BC><U+03B1><U+03C1><U+03B9><U+03BD><U+03AE> |language=Greek}}</ref> 

On March 26, 2005 Nea Salamina gave friendly football match against the Turkish Cypriot [[Yeni Mosque]] (within the transcription Oulousoi), at [[Ammochostos Stadium]], beating with 6-0. It was the first match between a Greek Cypriot and a Turkish Cypriot clubs after 50 years. 2500 fans attended the race who sat in the stands together sending a message of peace. In the game was attended by representatives of the political leadership of both communities, local and sports authorities and the Church.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://admin.typos.com.cy/nqcontent.cfm?a_id=51153 |title=<U+03A0><U+03B5><U+03BD><U+03AE><U+03BD><U+03C4><U+03B1> <U+03C7><U+03C1><U+03CC><U+03BD><U+03B9><U+03B1> <U+03BC><U+03B5><U+03C4><U+03AC>, <U+03C4><U+03BF> <U+03C0><U+03BF><U+03B4><U+03CC><U+03C3><U+03C6><U+03B1><U+03B9><U+03C1><U+03BF> <U+03BC><U+03B1><U+03C2> <U+03AD><U+03BD><U+03C9><U+03C3><U+03B5>... |accessdate=2012-08-19 |date=2005-03-26 |work= |publisher=typos.com.cy |language=Greek}}</ref>

== Women's Soccer ==
In 2006, Nea Salamis created female football department, which took part in the women's events. In the first inning to 2006-2007 [[Cypriot First Division (women)|Cypriot First Division]], took third place and qualified for the [[Cypriot Women's Cup|cup]] final, where he lost 1-3 against [[AEK Kokkinochorion]] in [[GSP Stadium]]. That same year won the [[Cypriot Women's Super Cup|Super Cup]] beating AEK Kokkinochorion with 2-1, in a game that was in [[Ammochostos Stadium]] in Larnaca.

In 2007-08, took second place. The same happened in 2008-09, losing the championship game to zero because of the champion [[Apollon Limassol (women)|Apollon Limassol]], since in their game with the home side Nea Salamis, the referee stopped the match due to excessive presence of fans compared to the capacity of the stadium. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cfa.com.cy/Gr/competitionstage/40/39/6/2008%20-%202009 |title=<U+03A0><U+03C1><U+03C9><U+03C4><U+03AC><U+03B8><U+03BB><U+03B7><U+03BC><U+03B1> <U+0393><U+03C5><U+03BD><U+03B1><U+03B9><U+03BA><U+03CE><U+03BD> <U+0391>' <U+039A><U+03B1><U+03C4><U+03B7><U+03B3><U+03BF><U+03C1><U+03AF><U+03B1><U+03C2> - <U+03A6><U+03AC><U+03C3><U+03B7> <U+0391>' |accessdate=2012-08-05 |date= |work= |publisher=[[Cyprus Football Association]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cfa.com.cy/Gr/competitionstage/40/39/6/2008%20-%202009 |title=<U+03A3><U+03B1><U+03BB><U+03B1><U+03BC><U+03AF><U+03BD><U+03B1>: <U+03A0><U+03BF><U+03B9><U+03BF> Fair Play <U+03B1><U+03C0><U+03CC> <U+0391><U+03C0><U+03CC><U+03BB><U+03BB><U+03C9><U+03BD> Ladies; |accessdate=2012-08-07 |date=2009-02-26 |work= |publisher=SigmaLive |language=Greek}}</ref> At the same time emerged as winter champions finished first at the end of the first round of the championship.

In 2008-2009, the footballer of Nea Salamis, Skevi Antoniou became the first scorer of [[Cypriot First Division (women)|Cypriot First Division]], scoring 64 goals <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cfa.com.cy/?lang=Gr&show=staticpage&PageID=281&CompetitionID=40 |title=<U+03A3><U+03BA><U+03CC><U+03C1><U+03B5><U+03C1> <U+0393><U+03C5><U+03BD><U+03B1><U+03B9><U+03BA><U+03B5><U+03AF><U+03BF><U+03C5> <U+03C0><U+03C1><U+03C9><U+03C4><U+03B1><U+03B8><U+03BB><U+03AE><U+03BC><U+03B1><U+03C4><U+03BF><U+03C2> 2008-2009|accessdate=2009-05-29|first=http://tools.wikimedia.de/~magnus/makeref.php |date= |work= |publisher=<U+039A><U+03C5><U+03C0><U+03C1><U+03B9><U+03B1><U+03BA><U+03AE> <U+039F><U+03BC><U+03BF><U+03C3><U+03C0><U+03BF><U+03BD><U+03B4><U+03AF><U+03B1> <U+03A0><U+03BF><U+03B4><U+03BF><U+03C3><U+03C6><U+03B1><U+03AF><U+03C4><U+03BF><U+03C5> |language=Greek}}</ref>.

The club was forced to shut down part of the women's football in 2010 for economic reasons.

